In a message to the Congress of the United States, President Barack Obama declares that the national emergency with respect to Zimbabwe is to continue beyond March 6, 2009. He states that the crisis caused by certain members of the Government of Zimbabwe and others to undermine democratic processes and institutions in the country has not been resolved. Obama believes that these actions and policies pose a continuing threat to the foreign policy of the United States, and therefore, it is necessary to maintain the sanctions in response to this threat. The message was published on March 4, 2009.